From: Sricharan R <r.sricharan@ti.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jul 2013 20:22:59 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 0394/1115] ARM: DRA7: Correct sdma sysc flags

SDMA IP does not have SIDLE/MSTANDBY SMART_XX
sysconfig options and these are reserved values.
So programming these wrong values results in the
SDMA IP not getting idled during lowpower transitions.

So removing those invalid entries.

Signed-off-by: Sricharan R <r.sricharan@ti.com>
(cherry picked from commit 0fe59750a760cbe63aa73bc0d03bdf568552ed4e)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c |    4 ++--
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c
index 06e1cd5..1e7783d 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c
@@ -324,8 +324,8 @@ static struct omap_hwmod_class_sysconfig dra7xx_dma_sysc = {
 			   SYSC_HAS_SIDLEMODE | SYSC_HAS_SOFTRESET |
 			   SYSS_HAS_RESET_STATUS),
 	.idlemodes	= (SIDLE_FORCE | SIDLE_NO | SIDLE_SMART |
-			   SIDLE_SMART_WKUP | MSTANDBY_FORCE | MSTANDBY_NO |
-			   MSTANDBY_SMART | MSTANDBY_SMART_WKUP),
+			   MSTANDBY_FORCE | MSTANDBY_NO |
+			   MSTANDBY_SMART),
 	.sysc_fields	= &omap_hwmod_sysc_type1,
 };
 
